{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In LangGraph every node reads from and writes to a single shared state object \u2014 a Python TypedDict that flows through the graph. This shared state is the primary coordination mechanism between agents: one node writes a result, and any downstream node can read it. The key insight is that "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "how writes are merged"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is configurable per field, which is what makes parallel agents safe \u2014 without careful reducer design, two agents writing the same field simultaneously will silently overwrite each other."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Shared State Architecture",
          "title": "Multiple agents read/write the shared TypedDict; annotated reducers control how concurrent writes merge"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Last-Write-Wins vs Reducer Fields"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every field in a LangGraph TypedDict uses one of two merge strategies:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Last-write-wins"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (the default) \u2014 the final node to return a value for that key wins. Safe only when exactly one node writes the field per graph step."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Annotated reducer"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 wrap the type with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Annotated[T, reducer_fn]"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ". LangGraph calls "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "reducer_fn(existing, new)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " to merge concurrent writes. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "operator.add"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is the most common choice for lists."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import operator\nfrom typing import Annotated\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\n\n\nclass AgentState(TypedDict):\n    # Last-write-wins: only one node should write this\n    task: str\n    final_summary: str\n\n    # Reducer: parallel agents can safely append\n    findings: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n    scores: Annotated[list[float], operator.add]\n    errors: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n\n    # Custom reducer: keep the highest confidence score seen\n    best_confidence: Annotated[float, max]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The custom "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "max"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " reducer on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "best_confidence"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " means that whichever agent returns the highest value wins \u2014 and it composes correctly with parallel writes because "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "max(a, b)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is associative and commutative."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Writing Custom Reducers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Any binary function "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "(existing, new) -> merged"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " works as a reducer. Three patterns cover most needs:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from typing import Annotated, TypeVar\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\n\n\ndef keep_latest(existing: T, new: T) -> T:\n    \"\"\"Identical to last-write-wins \u2014 useful when you want to be explicit.\"\"\"\n    return new\n\n\ndef deduplicate(existing: list, new: list) -> list:\n    \"\"\"Append only items not already present (by value).\"\"\"\n    seen = set(map(str, existing))\n    return existing + [x for x in new if str(x) not in seen]\n\n\ndef merge_dicts(existing: dict, new: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Shallow merge: new values overwrite existing keys.\"\"\"\n    return {**existing, **new}\n\n\nclass RichState(TypedDict):\n    # Standard append\n    messages: Annotated[list[str], lambda a, b: a + b]\n    # Dedup-aware append\n    sources: Annotated[list[str], deduplicate]\n    # Dict merge\n    metadata: Annotated[dict, merge_dicts]\n    # Explicit latest\n    current_step: Annotated[str, keep_latest]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parallel Agents Writing Safely"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When LangGraph fans out to multiple nodes via "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Send"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", each agent runs concurrently and returns a partial state update. LangGraph collects all updates and applies the reducers in the order they complete. With "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "operator.add"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the merge is correct regardless of completion order:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import operator\nfrom typing import Annotated\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\nfrom langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\nfrom langgraph.constants import Send\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\n\nclass ParallelState(TypedDict):\n    topics: list[str]\n    findings: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]   # safe for parallel writes\n    final: str\n\n\n_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n\ndef dispatcher(state: ParallelState) -> list[Send]:\n    \"\"\"Fan out: one research agent per topic.\"\"\"\n    return [Send(\"research\", {\"topic\": t}) for t in state[\"topics\"]]\n\n\ndef research(state: dict) -> dict:\n    resp = _llm.invoke(f\"Give one key fact about: {state['topic']}\")\n    # Each agent returns a single-element list\n    # LangGraph's operator.add reducer concatenates them all\n    return {\"findings\": [resp.content]}\n\n\ndef synthesise(state: ParallelState) -> dict:\n    combined = \"\\n\".join(state[\"findings\"])  # all findings already merged\n    resp = _llm.invoke(f\"Summarise:\\n{combined}\")\n    return {\"final\": resp.content}\n\n\nbuilder = StateGraph(ParallelState)\nbuilder.add_node(\"dispatch\", dispatcher)\nbuilder.add_node(\"research\", research)\nbuilder.add_node(\"synthesise\", synthesise)\nbuilder.set_entry_point(\"dispatch\")\nbuilder.add_edge(\"research\", \"synthesise\")\nbuilder.add_edge(\"synthesise\", END)\ngraph = builder.compile()\n\nresult = graph.invoke({\"topics\": [\"photosynthesis\", \"quantum tunnelling\", \"CRISPR\"], \"findings\": [], \"final\": \"\"})\nprint(result[\"final\"])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Checkpointing: Persisting Shared State"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LangGraph saves the full state snapshot after every node completes. A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "MemorySaver"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keeps snapshots in RAM (useful for testing); "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "SqliteSaver"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " persists to disk; "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "PostgresSaver"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to a database. Resuming from a checkpoint rehydrates the state and re-enters the graph from the last completed node:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import MemorySaver\nfrom langgraph.checkpoint.sqlite import SqliteSaver\n\n# Development: in-memory checkpoints\nmemory = MemorySaver()\ndev_graph = builder.compile(checkpointer=memory)\n\n# Production: SQLite-backed checkpoints\nwith SqliteSaver.from_conn_string(\":memory:\") as saver:\n    prod_graph = builder.compile(checkpointer=saver)\n    config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"run-001\"}}\n\n    # First invocation\n    result = prod_graph.invoke(\n        {\"topics\": [\"AI safety\"], \"findings\": [], \"final\": \"\"},\n        config=config,\n    )\n\n    # Resume from checkpoint (e.g. after a crash)\n    # Graph re-enters from the last completed node\n    state = prod_graph.get_state(config)\n    print(\"Checkpoint step:\", state.next)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Missing reducer on list fields"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 if two parallel nodes return "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "{\"findings\": [x]}"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " without "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "operator.add"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", only the last-to-finish agent's value survives. Always use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Annotated[list, operator.add]"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for fields written by multiple agents."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Non-associative custom reducers"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 reducers are applied in completion order, which is non-deterministic for parallel branches. Make reducers commutative and associative (like "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "operator.add"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " or "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "max"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ") so the result is the same regardless of order."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Large state objects"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 the entire state is checkpointed on every step. Keep payloads small; store large artefacts (embeddings, images, long documents) by reference ID and retrieve them inside the node that needs them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Mutating state in place"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 nodes must return a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "dict"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " of updates, not modify the state argument directly. Mutations bypass the reducer pipeline and can corrupt checkpoints."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scoped State: Private vs Shared Fields"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not every field needs to be visible to all agents. When using "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Send"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the payload dict passed to a worker node is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "private"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to that invocation \u2014 it does not appear in the graph's main state. This lets you pass per-task context without polluting the shared namespace:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.constants import Send\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\n\nclass SharedState(TypedDict):\n    \"\"\"Fields visible to all nodes.\"\"\"\n    query: str\n    results: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n\n\n# Private worker state \u2014 not in SharedState\nclass WorkerPayload(TypedDict):\n    sub_query: str       # scoped to this worker only\n    worker_id: str\n\n\n_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n\ndef make_worker():\n    def worker(payload: WorkerPayload) -> dict:\n        # payload fields are private; only 'results' goes back to shared state\n        resp = _llm.invoke(payload[\"sub_query\"])\n        print(f\"[{payload['worker_id']}] done\")  # local only, not in state\n        return {\"results\": [resp.content]}\n    return worker\n\n\ndef coordinator(state: SharedState) -> list[Send]:\n    sub_queries = [\n        f\"{state['query']} \u2014 aspect {i}\"\n        for i in range(1, 4)\n    ]\n    return [\n        Send(\"worker\", WorkerPayload(sub_query=q, worker_id=f\"w{i}\"))\n        for i, q in enumerate(sub_queries)\n    ]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inspecting and Updating State Mid-Run"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LangGraph exposes "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "graph.get_state(config)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "graph.update_state(config, values)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for external inspection and human-in-the-loop corrections. This is useful for debugging, step-through testing, or injecting a human correction before the next node executes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import MemorySaver\n\nmemory = MemorySaver()\ngraph = builder.compile(checkpointer=memory, interrupt_before=[\"synthesise\"])\nconfig = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"debug-run\"}}\n\n# Run until the interrupt (just before 'synthesise')\ngraph.invoke({\"topics\": [\"fusion energy\"], \"findings\": [], \"final\": \"\"}, config=config)\n\n# Inspect what's in state\nstate = graph.get_state(config)\nprint(\"findings so far:\", state.values[\"findings\"])\n\n# Inject a human correction before synthesis\ngraph.update_state(\n    config,\n    {\"findings\": state.values[\"findings\"] + [\"[human note] Also consider safety concerns.\"]},\n)\n\n# Resume from the interrupt\nfinal = graph.invoke(None, config=config)\nprint(final[\"final\"])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "State Versioning with Schema Evolution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you add new fields to a TypedDict schema, old checkpoints won't have those keys. Provide a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "state_schema"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "total=False"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (all fields optional) or use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": ".get()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with defaults inside nodes. For breaking removals, write a migration that updates checkpointed snapshots before deploying:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from typing_extensions import TypedDict, NotRequired\n\n\nclass AgentStateV2(TypedDict):\n    # v1 fields\n    query: str\n    findings: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n    final: str\n    # v2 additions \u2014 optional so old checkpoints deserialise cleanly\n    confidence_scores: NotRequired[Annotated[list[float], operator.add]]\n    metadata: NotRequired[Annotated[dict, lambda a, b: {**a, **b}]]\n\n\ndef synthesis_v2(state: AgentStateV2) -> dict:\n    findings = state.get(\"findings\", [])    # safe on old checkpoints\n    scores = state.get(\"confidence_scores\", [])\n    # ... synthesise ...\n    return {\"final\": \"synthesis result\"}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Shared State Interactions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The reducer logic is pure Python \u2014 test it separately from the LLM calls. Then test the full graph with a mocked LLM to verify state merges correctly across parallel branches:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import pytest\n\n\ndef test_deduplicate_reducer():\n    assert deduplicate([\"a\", \"b\"], [\"b\", \"c\"]) == [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]\n    assert deduplicate([], [\"x\"]) == [\"x\"]\n    assert deduplicate([\"x\"], [\"x\"]) == [\"x\"]   # no duplicate\n\n\ndef test_parallel_findings_merge():\n    from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n    from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import MemorySaver\n\n    mock_llm = MagicMock()\n    mock_llm.invoke.side_effect = [\n        MagicMock(content=\"finding A\"),\n        MagicMock(content=\"finding B\"),\n        MagicMock(content=\"synthesis\"),\n    ]\n    with patch(\"ChatAnthropic\", return_value=mock_llm):\n        g = builder.compile(checkpointer=MemorySaver())\n        out = g.invoke(\n            {\"topics\": [\"X\", \"Y\"], \"findings\": [], \"final\": \"\"},\n            config={\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"test\"}},\n        )\n    # Both parallel research nodes appended via operator.add\n    assert len(out[\"findings\"]) == 2\n    assert \"finding A\" in out[\"findings\"]\n    assert \"finding B\" in out[\"findings\"]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LangGraph's shared state is a TypedDict that flows through all nodes \u2014 the primary coordination mechanism between agents."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fields without an annotation use last-write-wins; fields with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Annotated[T, reducer]"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " merge concurrent writes via the reducer function."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "operator.add"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for lists written by parallel agents; use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "max"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " / "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "min"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for scalar extrema; write custom reducers for dedup or dict merge."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reducers must be commutative and associative because parallel branches complete in non-deterministic order."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "SqliteSaver"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " or "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "PostgresSaver"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " in production to persist state snapshots and enable graph resumption after crashes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}